        "start_line": 444,
        "end_line": 475,
        "caption": "Known high-velocity objects suspected to be runaways from thermonuclear supernovae. Uncertainties are $1\\sigma$ (middle 68\\%). Objects in bold are new discoveries. We also list previously known $\\rm D^6$ stars (\\citetalias{Shen2018}) and LP~40-365 stars \\citep{Raddi2019}, as well as the one known high-velocity helium star US~708 \\citep{Geier2015}, the oxygen-atmosphere WD~J1240 \\citep{Gansicke2020}, and the object J1637 \\citep{Raddi2019}, which may be a $\\rm D^6$ star or in the same class as J1240.",
        "label": "tab:all_systems"
      },
      "source_path": "literature/2306.03914/arxiv_source/manuscript.tex",
